    {
      "name": "Solo Monster",
      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "keywords": [],
        "power": null,
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>At the end of each of their turns, the ashen hoarder can take [[/damage 10]] damage to end one effect on them that can be ended by a saving throw. This damage can't be reduced in any way.</p><p>The ashen hoarder can take two turns each round. They can't take turns consecutively.</p>",
          "director": ""
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bladed Body",
      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "keywords": [],
        "power": null,
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>An adjacent enemy who grabs the ashen hoarder or uses a melee ability against them takes [[/damage 3]] damage.</p>",
          "director": ""
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Soul Singularity",
      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "keywords": [],
        "power": null,
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>When the ashen hoarder is reduced to 0 Stamina, they explode in a swirling singularity of bone shards and soul energy. Each creature within 5 squares of the ashen hoarder who has M &lt; 3 takes [[/damage 11 corruption]] damage. A creature killed by this damage has their soul sucked into the vortex and lost somewhere in the Abyssal Wasteland, and can't be brought back to life until their soul is recovered.</p>",
          "director": ""
        }
      }
    },
